'''剛果國際協會'''（法語：Association internationale du Congo）是[[比利時|比利時]][[利奧波德二世|利奧波德二世]]於1879年11月17日成立的一個協會。<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.britannica.com/topic/Association-Internationale-du-Congo|title=Association Internationale du Congo|website=Encyclopædia Britannica|date=22 March 2007|accessdate=2020-10-20|archive-date=2015-08-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150804065518/https://www.britannica.com/topic/Association-Internationale-du-Congo|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=PR8jAQAAIAAJ&q=17++1879|title=Memo from Belgium|last=|first=|date=1978|publisher=|isbn=|location=|pages=210|language=en|access-date=2020-10-20|archive-date=2022-05-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220521232138/https://books.google.com/books?id=PR8jAQAAIAAJ&q=17++1879}}</ref>它取代了比利時上剛果研究委員會<ref name="#1">{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=_5EoYIaHk70C&pg=PA63|title=Congo: Democratic Republic - Republic|last=Rorison|first=Sean|date=2012-07-20|publisher=Bradt Travel Guides|isbn=9781841623917|location=|pages=63|language=en|access-date=2020-10-20|archive-date=2022-05-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220521083829/https://books.google.com/books?id=_5EoYIaHk70C&pg=PA63}}</ref>，後者是為開採剛果而成立的[[國際非洲協會|國際非洲協會]][[傀儡組織|傀儡組織]]的一部分。剛果國際協會的目標是建立對剛果盆地的控制並開發其經濟資源。<ref name="#1"/>柏林會議認識到該社會對其控制的領土擁有主權，並於1885年8月1日，即[[柏林西非會議|柏林西非會議]]閉幕四個半月後，利奧波德國王在剛果的副總幹事宣布該社會和領土從此它被佔領了，被稱為“[[剛果自由邦|剛果自由邦]]”。<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Cornelis|first=S.|date=1991|title=Stanley au service de Léopold II: La fondation de l'Etat Indépendant du Congo (1878-1885)|url=|journal=In Cornelis, S. (Ed.), H.M. Stanley: Explorateur Au Service du Roi. Pp. 41-60. Tervuren: Royal Museum for Central Africa.|volume=|pages=53–54|via=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=u4X1CAAAQBAJ&pg=PA26|title=Legal problems arising from the United Nations military operations in the Congo|last=Simmonds|first=R.|date=2012-12-06|publisher=Springer|isbn=9789401192675|location=|pages=26|language=en|access-date=2020-10-20|archive-date=2022-05-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220521083857/https://books.google.com/books?id=u4X1CAAAQBAJ&pg=PA26}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Katzenellenbogen|first=S.|date=1996|title=It didn't happen at Berlin: Politics, economics and ignorance in the setting of Africa's colonial boundaries.|url=|journal=In Nugent, P. And Asiwaju, A. I. (Eds.), African Boundaries: Barriers, Conduits and Opportunities. Pp. 21-34. London: Pinter.|volume=|pages=|via=}}</ref>

